<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-03 12:46:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sergei Fedorov Suspended for 5 Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Sergei Fedorov of the Detroit Red Wings was  
suspended for five games without pay today for slashing Zdeno Chara 
of the New York Islanders. 
</P>
<P>
	Sitting out those games will cost the forward $386,178.  
</P>
<P>
	Federov's attack came with six minutes left in Saturday's game  
on the Islanders' home ice. Fedorov swung his stick with his right 
hand and struck Chara on the neck. Chara collapsed to the ice and 
remained there for several minutes. Fedorov was assessed a match 
penalty for deliberately injuring an opponent. 
</P>
<P>
	Fedorov is classified as a repeat offender. He was suspended two  
games last March 26 for a hit from behind on Jason Marshall of 
Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
	``While Mr. Fedorov acknowledges and regrets the severity of his  
action, the league has made clear this season there is no 
acceptable explanation for administering blows to the head,'' said 
Colin Campbell, the league's senior vice-president and director of 
hockey operations, after conducting a hearing today. ``This 
suspension also reaffirms the league's position that every player 
is accountable for his stick and that reckless, dangerous use of 
the stick will be met with severe consequences.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Fedorov will miss Detroit's game at Phoenix on Friday night,  
plus contests at Anaheim on Sunday, at Los Angeles on Tuesday, at 
San Jose on March 12 and at Colorado on March 14. He will be 
eligible to return March 17 against Phoenix. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
