least two weeks of spring training with a stress fracture of his 
right foot. 
</P>
<P>
	Whiten, expected to open the season as a reserve, complained  
about pain in the foot and underwent tests Monday, the club 
announced on Wednesday at Winter Haven, Fla. 
</P>
