<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Most Uninterested in Monica's Book </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some results from the Gallup Poll about Monica Lewinsky,  
President Clinton and the release of her televised interview and 
book. When results do not total 100 percent, the remainder did not 
know or offered no answer. 

</P>
<P>
	--Would you personally be interested in reading the book about  
Monica Lewinsky when it comes out? 
</P>
<P>
	Yes, would be interested, 8 percent; no, would not be  
interested, 92 percent. 

</P>
<P>
	--Based on what you have seen in the news, how do you feel toward  
the following people -- very sympathetic, somewhat sympathetic, 
somewhat unsympathetic, very unsympathetic: 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton: Very sympathetic, 11 percent; somewhat sympathetic, 20  
percent; somewhat unsympathetic, 18 percent; very unsympathetic, 47 
percent. The number of people who are very unsympathetic toward 
Clinton has risen from a third to almost half in just over a month. 
</P>
<P>
	Hillary Clinton: Very sympathetic, 37 percent; somewhat  
sympathetic, 32 percent; somewhat unsympathetic, 10 percent; very 
unsympathetic, 17 percent. These numbers are fairly consistent with 
results a month ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Lewinsky: Very sympathetic, 3 percent; somewhat sympathetic,  
23 percent; somewhat unsympathetic, 24 percent; very unsympathetic, 
46 percent. The number of people who are very unsympathetic toward 
Ms. Lewinsky has increased by 20 percentage points since that 
question was asked during the impeachment trial. 

</P>
<P>
	--Thinking about Bill Clinton as a person, do you have a positive  
or negative opinion of him? 
</P>
<P>
	Positive, 32 percent; negative, 60 percent. In December, people  
in a Gallup poll were about equally divided on how they view 
Clinton. 

</P>
<P>
	The Gallup Poll of 1,013 people was taken Friday through Sunday  
and has an error margin of plus or minus 3 percentage points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
