<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock 
Market, and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Jones Apparel Group Inc. fell 3 3/16 to 22 3/4.  
</P>
<P>
 *Nine West Group rose 1/16 to 22 7/8. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones Apparel agreed to buy footwear and accessories  
manufacturer Nine West for $885 million. 

</P>
<P>
 *Kmart Corp. fell 3/16 to 17 1/2.    	
</P>
<P>
	The nation's third-largest retailer earned 65 cents a share,  
beating Wall Street's expectations of 61 cents. 

</P>
<P>
 *Monsanto Co. rose 2 1/4 to 46 5/8.  
</P>
<P>
 *DuPont fell 1 1/16 to 50 5/4. 
</P>
<P>
	Monsanto is in talks to be acquired by DuPont, according to  
executives who have been briefed on the negotiations, the New York 
Times reported Wednesday. A Monsanto spokesman said the company has 
``a long-standing policy not to comment on speculation.'' 

</P>
<P>
 *Pall Corp. fell 4 13/16 to 16 1/2.    	
</P>
<P>
	The filtration and separations company reported disappointing  
fiscal second-quarter earnings and said it plans to cut costs in 
response to difficult market conditions. Earnings for the period 
ended Jan. 30 fell to 15 cents a share from year-ago's 22 cents and 
below First Call Corp.'s average forecast of 19 cents a share. 

</P>
<P>
 *Tiffany rose 2 1/8 to 61.    	
</P>
<P>
	The upscale jeweler reported fourth-quarter net income rose 27  
percent to $1.49 a share, from $1.17 a share. The results were 7 
cents a share higher than analysts had estimated. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Cyberian Outpost Inc. rose 6 3/8 to 22 1/2.    	
</P>
<P>
	The Internet computer products retailer expects to report an  
increase in fourth-quarter revenues to $33 million from $8.1 
million a year ago. 

</P>
<P>
 *Navarre Corp. rose 5/16 to 15 1/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	The company's majority-owned NetRadio is set to issue a $37.4  
million initial public offering. 

</P>
<P>
 *StaffMark Inc. fell 4 5/16 to 8 1/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	The staffing services company expects first-quarter earnings of  
10 cents to 13 cents a share, lower than analysts' estimates of 35 
cents a share, as a result of a lower demand from finance, banking 
and legal clients and lower growth from its IntelliMark unit's 
domestic information technology staffing business. The company also 
expects its 1999 earnings to be between 20 cents and 24 cents a 
share below analysts' estimates of $1.89 a share for the same 
reasons. 

</P>
<P>
 *Concentra Managed Care, Inc. rose 3 1/16 to 14 11/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The troubled managed-care company agreed to be acquired by  
buyout firm Welsh, Carson, Anderson &AMP; Stowe for $772 million plus 
assumed debt of $328 million. Welsh Carson, which already owns 15 
percent of Concentra, will make the acquisition through its Yankee 
Acquisition Corp. unit. 

</P>
<P>
 *Alpha Industries Inc. rose 4 to 18 1/4.    	
</P>
<P>
	The company expects to earn about 51 cents a share in the fourth  
quarter ending March 28, including a tax benefit of 20 cents a 
share, which is in line with analysts' estimates. 

</P>
<P>
 *Modtech Holdings Inc. fell 5 1/8 to 9 5/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The maker of modular classrooms on Tuesday reported  
fourth-quarter earnings of 19 cents a share, down from 31 cents a 
year ago, citing the California legislature's delay in allocating 
funds for school construction. 

</P>
<P>
 *Wall Data Inc. fell 4 3/4 to 14 1/2.    	
</P>
<P>
	The software company restated third-quarter earnings at 30 cents  
a share, down from an originally reported 40 cents after deciding 
to exclude revenue from a sale between a German unit and a 
reseller. 

</P>
<P>
                               *AMEX    	

</P>
<P>
 *Audio Book Club fell 3/8 to 10 13/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The company agreed with Lycos to promote audiobooks on the Lycos  
Internet network. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
