<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Higher; Gold Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was up against other major currencies  
in European trading today. Gold was mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0900, down from 1.0927 Tuesday. The  
dollar was quoted at 121.22 Japanese yen, up from 120.60. At midday 
in New York, the euro was quoted at $1.0888 and the dollar was 
quoted at 121.65 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Tuesday: 1.4577  
Swiss francs, up from 1.4567; 1.5237 Canadian dollars, up from 
1.5230. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6170, up from $1.6128. In New  
York, the pound was quoted at $1.6133. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 
</P>
<P>
	--1.7943 German marks, up from 1.7899  
</P>
<P>
	--6.0180 French francs, up from 6.0031  
</P>
<P>
	--2.0218 Dutch guilders, up from 2.0168  
</P>
<P>
	--1,776.39 Italian lire, up from 1,772.01  
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $286.80 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$287.60 on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $286.10, down from $287.90.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold rose $0.30 in Hong Kong to close at $286.55.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.25 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.46. 
</P>
