<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Greenspan: Caution on Budget Surplus  
</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan  
tackled the problem of saving budget surplus money today before a 
House Commerce subcommittee. He said today's surpluses must be 
saved if they're to help fund Social Security later, when baby 
boomers need it. He mentioned alternatives of using funds for 
startups of private investment accounts, or paying down the 
national debt, making continued surpluses more likely. Whatever 
path is taken, he said, the important thing is national savings. 

</P>
<P>
	Stocks End Mixed; Dow Off 21.73  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks ended mixed today after technology shares  
rallied from a deep slump in the final hour, pulling broad market 
indexes up with them. The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 
21.73 at 9,275.88. The blue-chip index swung widely, rising as much 
as 40 points and shedding as much as 86 before trimming its losses 
in the final 30 minutes. The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite 
index rose 6.17 to 2,265.20. 

</P>
