<HEADLINE> American Spirit Wins Baldwin Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- American Spirit, a relatively obscure  
member of trainer Bob Baffert's cast of 3-year-olds, won 
Wednesday's $115,500 Baldwin Stakes on the turf at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
	Sent off at 14-1, American Spirit finished a neck in front of  
30-1 longshot Chomper, with favored Impressive Grades another head 
back in third. 
</P>
<P>
	Emile Ramsammy rode American Spirit, who won only one of five  
starts on the dirt but now has a first and a second in two starts 
on grass. 
</P>
<P>
	The winning time over the 6 1/2 furlongs at Santa Anita was 1:13  
4-5. 
</P>
<P>
	American Spirit, who carried 114 pounds in the race for  
3-year-olds, paid $31.20, $16.60 and $7.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Chomper, ridden by Chris McCarron and carrying 115, paid $23.80  
and $16.40. Impressive Grades, Corey Black and 118, paid $3.80. 
</P>
</TEXT>
