<HEADLINE> Lomas Brown Going to Browns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHANDLER, Ariz. (AP) -- A day after seemingly changing his mind  
about leaving the Arizona Cardinals, tackle Lomas Brown signed a 
three-year contract Wednesday with the Cleveland Browns. 
</P>
<P>
	The $10.75 million deal included a $3 million signing bonus.  
</P>
<P>
	During a news conference in the backyard of Brown's home in  
suburban Phoenix, he signed a contract that had been faxed to him 
by the Browns. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown, 26, had been expected to sign Tuesday with the expansion  
team but his agent, Lamont Smith, spent much of the day in new 
negotiations with the Cardinals. 
</P>
<P>
	A fixture at left tackle with the Cardinals the last three  
seasons, Brown reconsidered his decision Tuesday after Arizona 
offered a $2 million signing bonus and a two-year deal said to be 
about the equal of Cleveland's first two years but with more money 
for the coming season. 
</P>
<P>
	With Brown gone, the Cardinals reportedly will concentrate on  
keeping free-agent linebacker Jamir Miller. 
</P>
<P>
	``I know something will happen within a week. I don't know  
what,'' Miller said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
