points and 12 rebounds, both season highs, as the Clippers remained 
winless. 
</P>
<P>
	Hubert Davis added 18 points and Steve Nash and Gary Trent had  
16 each to help the Mavericks to their fifth victory in seven 
games. 
</P>
<P>
	Maurice Taylor's 18 points and 13 rebounds paced the Clippers,  
who fell to 0-13 and remain the only NBA team without a victory. 
The 1988-89 Miami Heat hold the league record for the worst start, 
opening 0-17. 
</P>
