	Reggie Miller had 21 points for the winners, with Chris Mullin  
adding 18 points, connecting on all five of his 3-point attempts. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Denver's seventh consecutive road loss and its seventh  
straight loss to Indiana. Denver got a season-high 28 points from 
Nick Van Exel. 
</P>
