<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the spotlight: James Van Der Beek  
</P>
<P>
	 *Image:* James Van Der Beek first caught the public's attention  
when the coming-of-age series ``Dawson's Creek'' debuted on the WB 
network last year. 
</P>
<P>
	``Some people may want to kill me after they hear this, but  
'Dawson's' is the first pilot I ever filmed, the first I ever 
auditioned for,'' he says. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* Van Der Beek was born on March 8, 1977, in  
Cheshire, Conn. He attended Cheshire Academy boarding school. 
Although he struggled with dyslexia, he won an academic scholarship 
and become a member of the National Honor Society. 
</P>
<P>
	He attended Drew University in Madison, N.J., but left school  
after winning his ``Dawson's Creek'' audition. 
</P>
<P>
	As the character Dawson Leery, Van Der Beek and his high school  
friends face the issues of sex, romance, fidelity and trust in an 
upper-middle class Massachusetts community. 
</P>
<P>
	``I laugh that Dawson has all these female fans, because I was  
just as big of a dork in high school and nobody had a crush on 
me,'' he says. 
</P>
<P>
	Van Der Beek also stars in the box-office hit, ``Varsity  
Blues,'' playing a high school football player who gets the chance 
to prove himself when the school's star quarterback is hurt. The 
film is set in a fictional, football-mad Texas town. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote: ``There was definitely a parallel between what happens  
to me in the movie and what happened to me with 'Dawson's Creek.' 
We had a scene in a restaurant in Austin, and I had to leave 'cause 
it's a college town and people had seen me and it got around and, 
um, it got nuts.'' 

</P>
