<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Seattle SuperSonics center Olden Polynice was  
fined $5,000 by the NBA on Wednesday for making an obscene gesture 
at fans after a game in Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
	Polynice, who left Sacramento to sign with the Sonics at the  
start of the season, was booed throughout Monday night's 105-102 
victory over the Kings. 
</P>
<P>
	``There isn't enough money in the world to take the kind of  
abuse I got,'' Polynice said. ``I gave these people five years of 
blood, sweat and tears, and this is what they give in return. 
</P>
<P>
	``These people were totally classless. They threw things at me.  
I'll tell you, if one of them had hit me, they were going to get 
dropped.'' 
</P>
