<HEADLINE> Dell Opens Online Superstore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROUND ROCK, Texas (AP) -- Dell Computer Corp. opened an online  
superstore today for consumers to buy computer-related products. 
</P>
<P>
	The store, which can be found at www.gigabuys.com, offers  
shoppers more than 30,000 computer-related products from many 
leading brands, including printers, digital cameras, scanners, 
games, software and business products, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Gigabuys.com offers all online computer shoppers a convenient  
way to buy all the software and accessories they need for their 
computers,'' said Michael Dell, chairman and CEO. 
</P>
<P>
	Dell currently sells more than $14 million in products each day  
over the Web, 25 percent of the company's business. The company 
plans to do 50 percent of its business online by the end of 2000, 
Dell officials said. 

</P>
